# Landing Page Conventions

The landing page is a **standalone dark-themed** showcase. The rest of the app uses light theme by default, so semantic color tokens resolve to light-mode values and will break the landing page.

## No Semantic Color Tokens

Never use NativeWind semantic color classes in landing components. They resolve to the wrong theme.

```tsx
// ❌ WRONG — resolves to light-mode colors (dark text on white bg)
className="text-primary"
className="bg-primary"
className="text-secondary"
className="border-tertiary"

// ✅ CORRECT — use direct hex/rgba in style prop
style={{ color: "#f9f9fb" }}
style={{ backgroundColor: "#0e101b" }}
style={{ color: "#b9c0d4" }}
style={{ borderColor: "rgba(64, 73, 104, 0.3)" }}
```

Layout-only classNames like `text-center`, `flex-1`, `flex-row` are fine.

## Color Reference

| Role | Value |
|---|---|
| Page background | `#0e101b` |
| Surface / card bg | `#111322` or `rgba(17, 19, 34, 0.6)` |
| Border | `rgba(64, 73, 104, 0.25–0.5)` |
| Text primary | `#f9f9fb` |
| Text secondary | `#b9c0d4` |
| Text tertiary | `#7d89b0` |
| Text muted | `#5d6b98` |
| Text faint | `#404968` |
| Brand blue | `#2f61f3` |
| Brand blue light | `#6895f8` |
| Accent green | `#10b981` |
| Accent purple | `#8b5cf6` |

## Web Tab Bar

`app-tabs.web.tsx` is a `<Slot />` passthrough on web. The landing page renders its own `<Header />` for navigation. Do not add a tab bar or nav drawer back — it conflicts with the landing header.

## Web-Only Styling

Use `Platform.OS === "web"` guards for CSS-only properties (gradients, backdrop-filter, transitions, animations, box-shadow). Always provide a native fallback.
